19/04/2011
SARAJEVO, Bosnia and Herzegovina (BiH) -- Police arrested a fellow officer Monday (April 18th) suspected of killing politician Ante Malic. Andrija Cerdic was detained near his family house in the village of Brisnik and was transferred to a hospital after trying to hurt himself. Malic, vice-president of the Croatian Peasant Party-New Croatian Initiative (HSS-NHI), was shot dead at a restaurant in Tomislavgrad at the weekend. (BHRT, Oslobodjenje, RTRS - 18/04/11)
